OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F357A1778526672
OL,3,CBan on release of sky lanterns and
OL,4,Cballoons proposed to protect wildlife
OL,6,FPlans to ban sky lanterns and balloons
OL,7,Fon land owned or managed by Cumberland
OL,8,FCouncil are due to be put forward.
OL,10,FThose proposing the motion say they
OL,11,Fpose risk to wildlife, livestock,
OL,12,Fproperty, farmland and the wider
OL,13,Fenvironment.
OL,15,FMembers of the full council are due to
OL,16,Fmeet at the Civic Centre in Carlisle
OL,17,Fon Tuesday and the move will be
OL,18,Fproposed by Bothel and Wharrels Green
OL,19,FParty councillor Jill Parry and
OL,20,FCockermouth Green Party councillor,
OL,21,FHelen Tucker.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G1/8
